entries.title: Luxury developers in Los Angeles bet someone will pay record prices for these condos
entries.description: Two Los Angeles developers hope to find buyers who will pay between $50 and a $100 million for a condo.

entries.title: AMD beats on sales and profit but warns of a 10% revenue decline in Q1
entries.description: AMD reported earnings as many of its rival chipmakers have stumbled in recent weeks, citing lower consumer demand for finished electronics.

entries.title: Alec Baldwin charged in 'Rust' shooting, prosecutors say he was 'distracted' during training
entries.description: Alec Baldwin has been officially charged for involuntary manslaughter following the announcement of the charges earlier this month.

entries.title: Fed expected to slow rate hiking to a quarter point but will stay unrelenting in inflation battle
entries.description: The Federal Reserve is expected to raise interest rates by a quarter point, and to signal it will stay vigilant in its fight against inflation.

entries.title: Silvergate Capital shares jump after BlackRock reports increased stake in the crypto bank
entries.description: Silvergate Capital jumped on Tuesday afternoon after BlackRock reported a 7% stake in the crypto bank.

entries.title: PayPal to lay off 2,000 employees in coming weeks, about 7% of workforce
entries.description: The payments giant PayPal adds to the spate of January tech layoffs with plans to cut 7%, CEO Dan Schulman announced Tuesday.

entries.title: General Motors doesn’t expect significant U.S. production of EVs until second half of year
entries.description: General Motors executives blamed U.S. battery cell plants for the company's slow rollout of EVs.

entries.title: James Gunn unveils DC's new film and TV plan, including fresh spins on Supergirl, Batman
entries.description: James Gunn announced a new slate of DC Extended Universe film and TV content including Superman, Batman and Supergirl projects.

entries.title: The Covid pandemic drives Pfizer's 2022 revenue to a record $100 billion
entries.description: Sales of Paxlovid surged to $18.9 billion in 2022, which was the first full year the antiviral pill was available.

entries.title: Adani’s battle with Hindenburg leaves investors sizing up exposure to the global banking sector
entries.description: While Gautam Adani received a vote of confidence from investors in its latest $2.5 public offering Tuesday, Wall Street is still sizing up his exposure to the global financial sector.

entries.title: Here's why Nike is suing Lululemon over shoe designs
entries.description: Nike is claiming patent infringement related to Lululemon's sale of the Chargefeel Mid, Chargefeel Low, Blissfeel and Strongfeel sneakers.

entries.title: UK pulls plug on top tech incubator after setting out to become 'world’s next Silicon Valley'
entries.description: The U.K. government diverted grant funding for the program to the startup incubation arm of Barclays Bank.

entries.title: IMF downgrades UK growth forecast, predicting only economic decline among G-7 countries
entries.description: The group expects the U.K. economy to contract by 0.6% this year where it previously forecast slight growth.

entries.title: Pfizer expects 2023 sales to decline by as much as 33% compared with record-breaking 2022
entries.description: The pharmaceutical company booked $100.3 billion for full-year 2022, an all-time high.

entries.title: Norway's gigantic sovereign wealth fund loses a record $164 billion, citing 'very unusual' year
entries.description: Norway's sovereign wealth fund on Tuesday reported a record loss of 1.64 trillion kroner ($164 billion) in 2022.

entries.title: Euro zone economy posts surprise expansion in the fourth quarter, curbing recession fears
entries.description: Euro zone narrowly avoided a contraction as energy prices provide some relief.

entries.title: Top U.S., Chinese and Russian officials tour Africa as global charm offensive gathers pace
entries.description: Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov, new Chinese Foreign Minister Qin Gang and U.S. Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen all embarked on African tours within the past month.

entries.title: China’s January factory activity returns to growth as economists cheer its reopening
entries.description: China's factory activity bounced back in January and expanded for the first time since September, data from the national bureau of statistics showed.

entries.title: Asia's chipmakers fall as Samsung sees worst quarterly profit in 8 years
entries.description: Chipmakers in Asia fell as South Korean conglomerate Samsung Electronics saw its worst profit decline since the third quarter of 2014.

entries.title: Nearly a year on from the supposed Russian exodus, most major companies have yet to withdraw
entries.description: After Russia invaded Ukraine in February 2022, companies across the G-7 and European Union announced plans to cease business operations in Russia.

entries.title: Swiss bank UBS gets a boost from higher interest rates, beats expectations in fourth quarter
entries.description: Swiss bank UBS reported $7.6 billion of  annual profit in full-year 2022, beating analyst expectations nearer to $7.3 billion.

entries.title: General Motors is set to report earnings before the bell. Here's what Wall Street expects
entries.description: The auto industry's earnings and forecasts are being closely watched by Wall Street for any signs of weakening consumer demand.

entries.title: McDonald's is about to report earnings. Here's what to expect
entries.description: McDonald's is set to report fourth-quarter earnings before the opening bell.

entries.title: Formula 1: Audi buys minority stake in Sauber ahead of 2026 F1 entry
entries.description: Audi is excepted to make its long-awaited entry into Formula 1 in 2026 and will be Sauber's strategic partner. It will use Ferrari power units in 2024 and 2025.

entries.title: China stocks are close to bull market highs after returning from Lunar New Year break
entries.description: China's onshore A-shares were hovering close to bull market territory on Monday, the first day after returning from the Lunar New Year holiday.

entries.title: Jim Chanos: Bear market is doing something unheard of in my career
entries.description: Famed short seller Jim Chanos sees an alarming trend in the market.

entries.title: IMF hikes global growth forecast as inflation cools and household spending surprises
entries.description: In its latest economic update, the institution said the global economy will grow 2.9% this year.

entries.title: Biden administration plans to end Covid public health emergency on May 11
entries.description: The Trump administration first issued the Covid emergency declarations in 2020.

entries.title: The rising cost of living isn't the only reason many in Asia are putting off retirement, Randstad says
entries.description: "Whether for meaning and purpose ... or to experience the challenges that come with a job, employment for many is more than just a paycheck," Randstad said.

entries.title: Trump sues Bob Woodward and publisher for $50 million over use of his interview recordings
entries.description: Trump claims he never agreed to allow audio of Woodward's tapes of his interviews with Trump to be sold to the public.
